 789:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****     This subsection provides a set of functions allowing to manage the SPI
 790:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****     data transfers.
 791:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 792:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****     [..] The SPI supports master and slave mode :
 793:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 794:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****     (#) There are two modes of transfer:
 795:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****        (++) Blocking mode: The communication is performed in polling mode.
 796:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****             The HAL status of all data processing is returned by the same function
 797:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****             after finishing transfer.
 798:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****        (++) No-Blocking mode: The communication is performed using Interrupts
 799:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****             or DMA, These APIs return the HAL status.
 800:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****             The end of the data processing will be indicated through the
 801:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****             dedicated SPI IRQ when using Interrupt mode or the DMA IRQ when
 802:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****             using DMA mode.
 803:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****             The HAL_SPI_TxCpltCallback(), HAL_SPI_RxCpltCallback() and HAL_SPI_TxRxCpltCallback() u
 804:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****             will be executed respectively at the end of the transmit or Receive process
 805:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****             The HAL_SPI_ErrorCallback()user callback will be executed when a communication error is
 806:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 807:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****     (#) APIs provided for these 2 transfer modes (Blocking mode or Non blocking mode using either I
 808:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c ****         exist for 1Line (simplex) and 2Lines (full duplex) modes.
 809:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 810:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_spi.c **** @endverbatim
